{{Notability|Web|date=August 2009}} {{Infobox website | name = Beach Volleyball Database | logo = Beach Volleyball Database.jpg | logo_size = 250px | screenshot = | caption = | url = [https://web.archive.org/web/20120207234250/http://www.bvbinfo.com/ www.bvbinfo.com] | alexa = {{DecreasePositive}} 878,261 ({{as of|2014|4|1|alt=April 2014}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web|url= http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/bvbinfo.com |title= Bvbinfo.com Site Info | publisher= [[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate= 2014-04-01 }}</ref> | commercial = | type = [[online resource]] | language = English | registration = | owner = Dennis Wagner ("Dr. Ono") | author = Dennis Wagner ("Dr. Ono") | launch date = {{launch date and age|1999|6|2|p=y}} | current status = active | revenue = | slogan = }}
The '''Beach Volleyball Database''' is an online [[website]] that holds extensive information about international [[beach volleyball]] players, tournaments and history. News are frequently updated, and the site has results for [[continent]]al and [[international]] tournaments. It is the only website of its kind in the sport of beach volleyball.
The press operations officer for the [[Association of Volleyball Professionals|AVP]], Tim Simmons, has said that the Beach Volleyball Database has had a major impact on the sport. Information that is now easily accessible through the website, used to take time consuming research through different sources. Now professional athletes have a chance to set long-term goals based on their long-term results in comparison to other professional beach volleyball players.<ref name=keck>Alan Keck, [http://www.bvbinfo.com/news.asp?ID=399 Beach Volleyball: Fan is a one-man, on-line encyclopedia on the sport], [[The Virginian Pilot]], 2002 (Beach Volleyball Database)</ref>
''Volleyball Magazine'' calls the website "a reliable source for entries and results."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://volleyballmag.com/avp-contract-042917/|title=Most AVP players acquiesce and sign contract, exclusivity agreement|date=April 29, 2017|first=Ed|last=Chan|work=Volleyball Magazine|accessdate=August 19, 2018}}</ref> The site also collaborates with the [[Fédération Internationale de Volleyball]] (FIVB) to provide tournament notes to the FIVB website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fivb.org/EN/BeachVolleyball/Document/2018_FIVB_BVB_Handbook_V1.pdf|title=FIVB 2018 Handbook Beach Volleyball|publisher=[[Fédération Internationale de Volleyball]]|date=February 20, 2018|accessdate=August 19, 2018}}</ref>
==History== The Beach Volleyball Database was launched online by Dennis Wagner on June 2, 1999.<ref name=about>Spotlight Beach Volleyball Database, [[About.com]], June 6, 1999{{cite web |url=http://volleyball.about.com/library/weekly/aa990606.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-07-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20011006045814/http://volleyball.about.com/library/weekly/aa990606.htm |archivedate=2001-10-06 |df= }}</ref> Wagner (nicknamed "Dr. Ono") operates the website on his own, for free.<ref name=keck/> He has spent thousands of hours on the database, from a computer terminal in his home.<ref name=about2>Spotlight Beach Volleyball Database - Why start the database?, June 6, 1999{{cite web|url=http://volleyball.about.com/sports/volleyball/library/weekly/aa990606-3.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-07-30 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010421201128/http://volleyball.about.com/sports/volleyball/library/weekly/aa990606-3.htm |archivedate=2001-04-21 |df= }}</ref>
